    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The single shortfall in Test conditions (achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted because bench testing at the primary ASTM F1717 condition confirms FEA predictions within pre-specified acceptance bounds for all three QoIs, and the clinical risk associated with the single-condition gap is judged low given the MEDIUM model influence and MEDIUM decision consequence. Overall credibility is sufficient to support regulatory submission for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design.",
